2019-06-05.text: I still miss him to this day. I keep thinking that maybe it wasn’t right for us back then, I would’ve gave him a million and one chances, because he was the first boy that I loved at the age of 13. At 16, I still thought we had something. I’m 22 now, and I thank him but fuck him.

One day it’s something cute, the next it’s accusations. He’s amazing, then he’s a total dick. I liked him one day, and hated him the next. It was just the most toxic thing I’ve experienced. I wished it didn’t end with him blocking me on everything

He accused me of talking to countless guys multiple of times, called me a slut and a whore. This kept going for 8 months before I got sick of it. I was on a school trip when he texted me a cute text, then I straight up told him he has to stop playing with me.

He got so mad at me but things change. I changed. I became shy and real insecure and was completely closed off. I couldn’t develop feelings towards anyone. He kept calling me a tease and tried to claim me as his even thought we weren’t officially dating.

We stopped talking, he started talking to all my friends. It hurt me. 2 years later, I got over it. A year after, he hit me up again, I was cool, I just wanted to be his friend but he wanted something more and I just wasn’t ready to be hurt by him again
